notesStmt.note: Former shelfmark: MS X893.7 K84 I142.

msContents.summary: Small, complete copy of the Qurʼān in a color-contrast inset paper technique.

supportDesc.extent: i, 546, iii foliated leaves : 93 x 60 (51 x 28) mm, bound to 96 x 60 x 36 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 11 lines per page; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written chiefly in naskh in black ink with sūrah titles in thuluth; pointed and vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Inset leaves so textblock is a lighter color; dual page illuminated first opening with the first sūrah written on a scalloped medallion lined in black with white flowers between each line, surrounding the medallion are flowers and vines in pink, purple, red, and green with an outside marginal illumination of a scalloped design chiefly in gold and blue with red, blue and purple flowers; sūrah headings are in a blue-lined rectangle, written in white ink lined in black on a gold background with polychrome vine and leaf designs; text divisions are marked by marginal medallions in gold and blue; verse endings marked by gold roundels; textblock border-ruled in gold and blue and page-opening frame-ruled in double black; readings in red.

binding.p: Lacquered covers; outside covers have gold flowers and vines on a black field with a frame of gold vines; inside covers are black with two gold painted frames around a central shape of a rectangle with quarter circles taken out of each corner and a half circle taken out of each long side.

origin.p: Item is undated; likely copied in the 18th century or 19th century.
